Based on the provided summary of the Emomemo app, I'll create a PlantUML diagram that illustrates the overall architecture and key components of the application. This diagram will show both static structure and dynamic interactions.

@startuml kaleidot725_Draft

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

package "Presentation Layer" {
  [ComposeMainActivity] as CMA
  [Navigation Compose] as NC
  [ViewModels] as VM
  [Jetpack Compose UI] as UI
  [TextEditor] as TE
}

package "Domain Layer" {
  [Use Cases] as UC
  [Domain Models] as DM
}

package "Data Layer" {
  [Repositories] as Repo
  database "Room Database" as RoomDB
}

cloud "Koin DI Container" as Koin

actor User

' Static relationships
User --> UI
CMA --> NC
NC --> UI
UI --> VM
UI ..> TE : uses
VM --> UC
UC --> Repo
Repo --> RoomDB
Koin ..> VM : injects
Koin ..> UC : injects
Koin ..> Repo : injects

' Dynamic interactions
UI -[#blue]-> VM : Intent
VM -[#blue]-> UI : State/SideEffect
VM -[#blue]-> UC : Execute
UC -[#blue]-> Repo : CRUD operations
Repo -[#blue]-> RoomDB : Query/Update
RoomDB -[#blue]-> Repo : Results
Repo -[#blue]-> UC : Data
UC -[#blue]-> VM : Results

note right of UI
  Jetpack Compose
  components for notebooks,
  memos, and CRUD operations
end note

note right of VM
  Implements MVI pattern
  using orbit-mvi
end note

note right of UC
  Encapsulates business logic
  e.g., CreateMemoUseCase,
  GetNotebooksUseCase
end note

note right of Repo
  Abstracts data access
  NotebookRepository,
  MemoRepository
end note

note bottom of Koin
  Dependency Injection
  for ViewModels, Use Cases,
  and Repositories
end note

@enduml